Bunge Ltd. (BG)  will invest $350 million
this year primarily in sugar-cane planting, the chief executive
officer of the companyâ€™s Brazil unit told  Valor Economico .  Bunge will plant about 300,000 hectares (741,000 acres) in
new areas and also do some replanting, unit CEO Pedro Parente
told the Sao Paulo-based newspaper.  The company also plans to boost electricity generation from
sugar-cane waste to 1,000 gigawatts per hour by 2013 from 270
gigawatts, Valor said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
